translated: Enhörning, Eric Hugo F:son, Consul, Norrköping, born on June 11, 1890 in Björkvik, Södermanland. First born to Consul C.F.A.E and H.H.F. Schubert. Married to Marianne von Rosen in 1918. Children: Gunvor born in 1925, married to Wallin, Lars-Erik born in 1927, currently a student. Studied at Hanover Institute of Business from 1907-1908, language studies in England from 1911-1912, and completed an agricultural degree from Ultuna Agricultural Institute in 1915. Worked with agriculture and forestry from 1908-1911, then became the director and manager of the company P.A. Enhörning & Co in Norrköping from 1917. Lithuanian Consul since 1936. Chairman of the Östergötland section of the Swedish Federation of Trade from 1943, member of the Norrköping Commercial Association from 1944, member of the Östergötland Chamber of Commerce in 1942, and member of the Norrköping Merchant Association. Member of the Norrköping yacht club, KAK, Norrköping Ski Club, and other societies. Chairman of the Östergötland section of the Swedish Motorboat Club in 1944, and chairman of the Norrköping Sailing Club in 1946, member of the board of the Bråviken sailing club. Member of the Freemasonry, Odd Fellows, W-Sex, and other associations. Also a member of the SMK (Swedish Motorboat Club) GNI in 1919, Norrköping SS G and Svmifb SM. His hobbies included sailing, curling, hunting, and fishing.

structured.name: Eric Hugo F Enhörning
structured.description: Eric Hugo F. Enhörning was a Swedish consul, born on June 11, 1890 in Björkvik, Södermanland. He was the first-born son of Consul C.F.A.E and H.H.F. Schubert and married Marianne von Rosen in 1918. He had two children, Gunvor and Lars-Erik. Eric Enhörning studied business at the Hanover Institute of Business from 1907-1908, language studies in England from 1911-1912, and earned an agricultural degree from Ultuna Agricultural Institute in 1915. He worked with agriculture and forestry from 1908-1911 before becoming the director and manager of the company P.A. Enhörning & Co in Norrköping from 1917. He became a Lithuanian Consul in 1936. Eric Enhörning was also active in various organizations, such as the Swedish Federation of Trade, Norrköping Commercial Association, and was a member of several yacht clubs, including the Norrköping Yacht Club and Bråviken Sailing Club. His hobbies included sailing, curling, hunting, and fishing.
